19/05/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- A foreign ministry delegation visiting Iraq held meetings Saturday (17 May) with representatives of the Kurdistan Democratic Party and the Patriotic Union of Kurdistan (PUK). The head of the delegation, Kadri Ecvet Tezcan, said the sessions were very beneficial to relations between the parties and the Turkish government. A major purpose of the visit was to conduct an on-the-spot study of problems faced by Turkmens in northern Iraq. During the meeting, PUK officials asked Turkey to open a general consulate in Kirkuk. (Anadolu Agency, NTV, AFP - 18/05/03)
